It's D, the others threw the below error when I tested it against the Cisco DevNet sandboxes:

"ietf-restconf:errors": {
 "error": [
 {
 "error-type": "application",
 "error-tag": "malformed-message",
 "error-path": "/Cisco-IOS-XE-native:native",
 "error-message": "missing element: native in /ios:native"
 }
 ]
 }
}

Selected Answer: B
In other example of:
https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/prog/configuration/1611/b_1611_programmability_cg/restconf_programmable_interface.html

We have:

# curl -i -k -X "PATCH" "https://10.85.116.30:443/restconf/data/Cisco-IOS-XE-native:native" \
> -H 'Content-Type: application/yang-data+json' \
> -H 'Accept: application/yang-data+json' \
> -u 'admin:admin' \
> -d $'{
> "native": {
> "logging": {
> "monitor": {
> "severity": "informational"
> }
> }
> }
> }'
